Sufago Technologies Project Proposal – Sauki Data International Upgrade Client: Sauki Data
Date: 28th November, 2025
1. Introduction Sauki Data has grown into a reliable VTU platform for bills payment, data, airtime,
and digital services in Nigeria. To scale further and meet increasing demand, this proposal outlines
a full upgrade to support international money transfers, multi-currency wallets, and international
calling services. 2. Scope of Upgrade (New Features) A. International Money Transfer
Send funds from Nigeria to Ghana, Cameroon, Kenya, and Uganda with wallet-to-wallet or mobile
money payouts.
B. Multi-Currency Wallet & Exchange
Support for USD, EUR, GBP (optional), GHS, KES, UGX, and XAF with live FX rates and in-app
conversion.
D. Security & Compliance
Transaction monitoring, anti■fraud checks, encrypted APIs, and multi-step verification.
E. Admin Dashboard Upgrade
International logs, liquidity management, rate control, user KYC, and analytics.
3. Project Timeline Month 1 – Research & Architecture: API research, currency systems,
compliance design.
Month 2 – Core Development: Wallet system, transfer engine, backend security.
Month 3 – API testings, dashboard upgrade.
Month 4 – Testing & Deployment: QA, load tests, security audit, launch.
4. Project Cost Total Cost: ■990,000
Covers backend, mobile integration, admin upgrade, APIs, security, testing, and documentation.
5. Benefits to the Client A. Wider Market Reach: Expand beyond Nigeria into 5 African countries.
B. Increased Revenue: Earn from transfer fees, FX margins, and international VTU commissions.
C. Competitive Advantage: Stand out as one of the few VTU platforms offering cross■border
payments.
D. Stronger Brand: Positions Sauki Data as a fintech leader.
E. Improved User Experience: Faster transfers, multi■currency flexibility, and secure operations.
6. Conclusion This upgrade transforms Sauki Data into a powerful cross■border fintech platform.
Sufago Technologies is ready to deliver this within 4 months at a cost of ■990,000.